    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-02-18T11:31:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-02-18T11:31:00-05:00" n="3"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d3">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/2–1854: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">United States Delegation at the Berlin
                            Conference</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-02-18T11:31:00-05:00"
                            >February 18, 1954—11:31 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 59. As soon as agreement on
                    Korea-Indochina resolution confirmed, we would like inform President <persName
                        corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName>. Would propose communicate to him through
                        <persName corresp="#p_BEO1">Briggs</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_YKT1">Young</persName>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d3fn1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_YKT1">Young</persName> was in Korea at this time as
                        Deputy U.S. Representative at the talks at Panmunjom concerning the holding
                        of a political conference on Korea; for documentation, see <ref
                            target="frus1952-54v15p1">volume <hi rend="smallcaps">xv</hi>
                        </ref>. These talks were discontinued following the decision at the Berlin
                        Conference to hold the Geneva Conference on Korea.</note> text of agreed <pb
                        facs="0044" n="18" xml:id="pg_18"/> resolution and points mentioned second
                    para <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 87,<note n="2" xml:id="d3fn2">
                        <p>Dated Feb. 18, from Berlin. The second paragraph read: <quote
                                rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“(1) Principle of no five power conference is upheld; (2) there
                                    is no promotion of Communist China to position of authority and
                                    prestige; (3) we are negotiating with Communist China only on
                                        <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> basis in relation to
                                    concrete local problems of war and peace where that regime is a
                                    necessary party; (4) composition for Korea is as we sought and
                                    India is excluded; and (5) our choice of place is accepted.”
                                    (396.1–BE/2–1854)</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                    </note> and would like to send Embassy Seoul for background guidance <gloss
                        target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 88.<note n="3" xml:id="d3fn3">
                        <ref target="#d2">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> Have you any objection?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
